description:
Both lichen_lora_l2_init() and lichen_lora_l2_start() are idempotent:

**lichen_lora_l2_init (lora_l2.c:276-286):**
```c
/* Idempotent: if already initialized, return success immediately.
 * This prevents EUI-64 regeneration on double-init (e.g., from both
 * main.c and NET_DEVICE_INIT calling this function).
 * SECURITY: Check under mutex to prevent TOCTOU race where two threads
 * both pass the check and generate different EUI-64 values. */
if (atomic_get(&lora_state.initialized)) {
    k_mutex_unlock(&lora_mutex);
    return 0;
}
```

**lichen_lora_l2_start (lora_l2.c:336-339):**
```c
if (atomic_get(&lora_state.running)) {
    k_mutex_unlock(&lora_mutex);
    return 0;  /* Already running */
}
```

**lichen_lora_l2_stop (lora_l2.c:393-396):**
```c
if (!atomic_get(&lora_state.running)) {
    k_mutex_unlock(&lora_mutex);
    return 0;
}
```

This is the correct pattern for system services that may be called from multiple initialization paths. The comments explain both the what (idempotent) and the why (prevents EUI-64 regeneration, TOCTOU races).
